  Examples of playlists sequenced using the proposed ap-
  
  The problem of sequencing tracks lends itself well to be
  formulated in a graph theory setting. The central step consists in mapping acoustic features into a Euclidean space so
  that songs that are fit to be sequenced next to each other are
  also close together in the feature space. Finding a good sequencing involves finding the shortest non-repeating path
  between all the songs.
  
